<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Dealing with a MSVC generated PDB, we encountered a type index with the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// value of: 0x0280xxxx where xxxx=0000.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// There is some documentation about type indices:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// https://llvm.org/docs/PDB/TpiStream.html</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A type index is a 32-bit integer that uniquely identifies a type inside</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of an object file’s .debug$T section or a PDB file’s TPI or IPI stream.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The value of the type index for the first type record from the TPI stream</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is given by the TypeIndexBegin member of the TPI Stream Header although</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in practice this value is always equal to 4096 (4096).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Any type index with a high bit set is considered to come from the IPI</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// stream, although this appears to be more of a hack, and LLVM does not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// generate type indices of this nature. They can, however, be observed in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Microsoft PDBs occasionally, so one should be prepared to handle them.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that having the high bit set is not a necessary condition to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// determine whether a type index comes from the IPI stream, it is only</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sufficient.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/debug-h/#a196897517069dda1bdb549e24468f7d7">LLVM&#95;DEBUG</a>(</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3240"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3241"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> LVLogicalVisitor::createParents(StringRef ScopedName, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/logicalview/lvelement">LVElement</a> &#42;Element) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3242"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For the given test case:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3243"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3244"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// struct S &#123; enum E &#123; ... &#125;; &#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3245"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// S::E V;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3246"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3247"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      0 | S&#95;LOCAL &#96;V&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3248"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//          type=0x1004 (S::E), flags = none</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3249"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 4100 | LF&#95;ENUM  &#96;S::E&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3250"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//          options: has unique name | is nested</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3251"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 4105 | LF&#95;STRUCTURE &#96;S&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3252"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//          options: contains nested class</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3253"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3254"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When the local &#39;V&#39; is processed, its type &#39;E&#39; is created. But There is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3255"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// no direct reference to its parent &#39;S&#39;. We use the scoped name for &#39;E&#39;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3256"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to create its parents.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3257"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3258"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The input scoped name must have at least parent and nested names.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3259"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Drop the last element name, as it corresponds to the nested type.</span></CodeLine>
